WEBVTT

00:08.486 --> 00:10.358
- If I knew putting
a crib together

00:10.401 --> 00:11.837
would be this complicated,

00:11.881 --> 00:13.665
I would've paid more attention
in my engineering class.

00:13.709 --> 00:15.580
- You just gotta havethe right tools.

00:15.624 --> 00:17.713
- [chuckles]

00:17.756 --> 00:19.584
And you've got them.

00:22.805 --> 00:24.198
I really appreciateyour help with this, Gabe.

00:24.241 --> 00:27.418
Between birthing classesand work squeezing me for OT--

00:27.462 --> 00:28.854
- Hey, don't let 'em
take advantage of you.

00:28.898 --> 00:30.204
You gotta fight 'em...
[phone chimes]

00:30.247 --> 00:31.727
And sometimes, Atul,
you gotta hit 'em in the head

00:31.770 --> 00:34.338
so they take you seriously.
- Oh, I gotta go.

00:34.382 --> 00:35.948
Amna's waiting for me.

00:35.992 --> 00:38.734
- You're leaving it like this?
- I'm sorry, man.

00:38.777 --> 00:40.562
I'll come back tomorrowto finish it.

00:40.605 --> 00:42.390
Amna's been dyingfor some pho gailately,

00:42.433 --> 00:44.087
and I promisedI'd take her out tonight.

00:44.131 --> 00:45.132
I'm coming, Amna!

00:45.175 --> 00:47.177
[foreboding music]

00:47.221 --> 00:49.179
- You're a lucky man, Atul.

00:49.223 --> 00:51.094
You're gonna have a family.

00:51.138 --> 00:58.101
♪

01:12.681 --> 01:13.986
- My dad will laugh
in my face

01:14.030 --> 01:15.771
if I tell him we're
getting married in a barn.

01:15.814 --> 01:17.642
- Not a barn barn--a nice barn

01:17.686 --> 01:19.209
with little lightsand a dance floor.

01:19.253 --> 01:21.081
- Yeah, come on, Tyler,
you only get married once--

01:21.124 --> 01:22.952
or twice, in my case.

01:22.995 --> 01:24.997
- Jerry's right, sweetie.
It's our wedding.

01:25.041 --> 01:26.999
- Yeah, sweetie,
I'm right on this.

01:27.043 --> 01:29.611
It's either the barn
or the doghouse.

01:29.654 --> 01:31.569
- Well, if you put it that way.

01:31.613 --> 01:33.136
[gunshots]

01:33.180 --> 01:34.572
- [gasps]

01:34.616 --> 01:37.488
[overlapping screams]

01:41.101 --> 01:44.016
[tense music]

01:44.060 --> 01:47.890
♪

01:48.630 --> 01:50.371
- I just came in
to baste the roast.

01:50.414 --> 01:51.676
I wasn't even five minutes.

01:51.720 --> 01:53.983
- I'm sure she's fine.

01:54.026 --> 01:55.550
Still no answer.

01:55.593 --> 01:57.813
You didn't hear a car pull up
or anything?

01:57.856 --> 02:00.381
- No, but the kitchen fan
was on.

02:00.424 --> 02:02.165
- Any chance Nelson
came home early?

02:02.209 --> 02:04.515
- No, I called him before you
came back from the market.

02:04.559 --> 02:06.169
He's still
at the doctor's office.

02:06.213 --> 02:07.779
- [sighs]
Oh, God.

02:07.823 --> 02:10.173
I shouldn't have left her
outside by herself.

02:10.217 --> 02:12.436
- It's okay, Marilou.
It's not your fault.

02:12.480 --> 02:13.524
[door clicks]

02:13.568 --> 02:14.917
- Hey, Dad.

02:14.960 --> 02:17.311
- [sighs]

02:17.354 --> 02:19.051
- Where were you?
- What?

02:19.095 --> 02:20.749
- Your grandma's been frantic
for half an hour.

02:20.792 --> 02:21.750
Why didn't you
answer your phone?

02:21.793 --> 02:23.404
- Well, I saw a hawk,

02:23.447 --> 02:25.928
and I thought it might have
been a northern goshawk, so I--

02:25.971 --> 02:27.625
- That's not an excuse.I've been trying to call you.

02:27.669 --> 02:29.018
- I turned off my phone.

02:29.061 --> 02:30.367
I didn't want
to scare the hawk.

02:30.411 --> 02:32.282
- The hawk--what about your grandma?

02:32.326 --> 02:34.502
You know you're not supposedto run off without telling us.

02:34.545 --> 02:36.678
[phone rings]

02:37.896 --> 02:40.769
LaCroix.I'm on my way.

02:42.379 --> 02:43.511
[phone beeps]

02:43.554 --> 02:46.340
- I'm sorry.

02:46.383 --> 02:47.863
- You know better.

02:47.906 --> 02:50.953
[soft dramatic music]

02:50.996 --> 02:52.868
We'll talk about thiswhen I get back,

02:52.911 --> 02:55.349
but until then, I'm sorry,but you're grounded.

02:55.392 --> 02:57.568
- What?

02:57.612 --> 02:58.787
[sighs]

02:58.830 --> 03:03.618
♪

03:03.661 --> 03:05.576
- [sighs]

03:06.621 --> 03:08.710
- This one's a fastball
from CID.

03:08.753 --> 03:11.016
Gabriel Clark, 27,
a police officer

03:11.060 --> 03:12.931
from Morristown, New Jersey,

03:12.975 --> 03:14.933
shot two New Jersey
state troopers last night

03:14.977 --> 03:16.544
in a diner along
with the fiancée

03:16.587 --> 03:18.328
of one of the troopers.

03:18.372 --> 03:19.938
- How'd the shooting go down?

03:19.982 --> 03:22.245
- Wits say Clark
entered the diner in uniform,

03:22.289 --> 03:24.334
walked up to the troopers,
and started shooting--

03:24.378 --> 03:27.511
head shots on all three.
No words exchanged, nothing.

03:27.555 --> 03:29.557
Then he walked out.

03:29.600 --> 03:32.255
- Cold blooded execution.

03:32.299 --> 03:35.084
And no effort
to disguise himself.

03:35.127 --> 03:37.304
Any history between Clark
and the victims?

03:37.347 --> 03:38.435
- None found.

03:38.479 --> 03:39.784
All we haveon Clark's personal life

03:39.828 --> 03:41.917
is he lives alone,no ex-wife, no kids.

03:41.960 --> 03:44.398
- Who was shot first?

03:44.441 --> 03:47.662
- State trooper Tyler Kubiak.
The woman is his fiancée.

03:47.705 --> 03:49.533
- Kubiak's the furthest
from the shooter.

03:49.577 --> 03:52.971
Would've been easier to start
with the other trooper.

03:53.015 --> 03:55.452
- Kubiak might have been
the main target.

03:55.496 --> 03:57.193
Start with him,
then the fiancée.

03:57.237 --> 03:59.587
- Maybe his beef
is with state police.

03:59.630 --> 04:01.284
Might not be
out of targets yet.

04:01.328 --> 04:03.068
- Clark has no historywith state police.

04:03.112 --> 04:04.548
He trained with Newark PD,

04:04.592 --> 04:05.680
didn't make it
through probation,

04:05.723 --> 04:07.421
and then transferred
to Morristown PD.

04:07.464 --> 04:08.900
- Big city to Mayberry--

04:08.944 --> 04:10.293
must have felt
like a step down.

04:10.337 --> 04:12.295
♪

04:12.339 --> 04:14.036
- Cops don't just snap.

04:14.079 --> 04:16.299
Newark PD might've detected
some weakness

04:16.343 --> 04:18.040
in his personality.

04:18.083 --> 04:20.390
Maybe that's why he never
got through probation.

04:20.434 --> 04:21.783
- I'll reach out to them.

04:21.826 --> 04:23.350
- You say,
"cops don't just snap."

04:23.393 --> 04:25.090
Is that supposed
to make us feel better.

04:25.134 --> 04:26.701
- It makes mefeel better about you.

04:26.744 --> 04:27.876
- What I'm trying to say

04:27.919 --> 04:30.792
is we're trained
to measure our response.

04:30.835 --> 04:32.968
We let the stress
of the job accumulate,

04:33.011 --> 04:35.710
sometimes what comes out
is depression--

04:35.753 --> 04:38.713
anger turned inward, suicide--

04:38.756 --> 04:42.151
or anger turned outward
toward the public.

04:42.194 --> 04:44.414
Officer Clark
didn't just wake up yesterday

04:44.458 --> 04:46.982
and decide to shoot
two state troopers.

04:47.025 --> 04:50.638
We find out what's behind it,
we find out his next move.

04:50.681 --> 04:52.596
♪

04:52.640 --> 04:54.598
- Hm. Sudoku.

04:54.642 --> 04:55.730
- I don't know.

04:55.773 --> 04:56.861
His fridge looks likeit just stepped

04:56.905 --> 04:58.167
out of a showroom.

04:58.210 --> 05:00.082
There's no leftovers,
no moldy pizza.

05:00.125 --> 05:01.736
Same deal
with his laundry room.

05:01.779 --> 05:02.867
No dirty clothes in the hamper,

05:02.911 --> 05:04.608
everything's polished
to a shine.

05:04.652 --> 05:06.654
- Maybe he's a germophobe.

05:07.481 --> 05:09.918
- Clark emptied out
his bank account two days ago--

05:09.961 --> 05:11.485
3 grand.
- He planned this.

05:11.528 --> 05:14.183
- He ran a tight ship--
no bounced checks,

05:14.226 --> 05:16.185
always paid off
his credit cards on time.

05:16.228 --> 05:18.448
Probably lived his whole life
between the hash lines

05:18.492 --> 05:21.364
like his choice of movies,
old-time westerns--

05:21.408 --> 05:22.844
"Shane," "Fort Apache"--

05:22.887 --> 05:26.195
good and bad with a hard line
between the two.

05:26.238 --> 05:28.197
- Don't talk to me
about westerns, bro.

05:36.423 --> 05:39.295
- "Veritas ante omnia."

05:39.339 --> 05:41.689
Truth before all.

05:41.732 --> 05:44.082
- Words to live by.

05:46.215 --> 05:49.218
- Hey, boss, Officer Hearn was
just telling me our boy Clark

05:49.261 --> 05:51.394
has six civilian complaintsin his file.

05:51.438 --> 05:53.004
- Yeah, he wrote a lot
of traffic tickets.

05:53.048 --> 05:54.397
I mean, he was just a hard-ass.

05:54.441 --> 05:56.051
You could be on fire
and go through a red light,

05:56.094 --> 05:57.618
and he'd escort you
to the hospital,

05:57.661 --> 05:59.533
but first he'd write you
that ticket.

05:59.576 --> 06:00.882
- Any beefswith state troopers?

06:00.925 --> 06:02.100
- Not that I heard.

06:02.144 --> 06:03.928
He never opened up to me
or anybody else

06:03.972 --> 06:05.887
in the department.

06:05.930 --> 06:08.063
- You know anything about this?
- No.

06:08.106 --> 06:09.717
He mentioned he had
a girlfriend in Newark,

06:09.760 --> 06:11.371
and I took his word for it,

06:11.414 --> 06:13.938
but he never told me her name
or showed me a photo, nothing.

06:13.982 --> 06:17.899
- Sir, that's our crib!
I live across the street.

06:23.121 --> 06:25.080
Gabe was helping me
put it together.

06:25.123 --> 06:27.822
I was over here yesterday,
and--

06:27.865 --> 06:29.432
God, I can't believehe finished it.

06:29.476 --> 06:30.607
- What do you mean?

06:30.651 --> 06:31.869
- I had to take my wife
out to dinner.

06:31.913 --> 06:33.305
We were only halfway done.

06:33.349 --> 06:35.220
It must have taken him
hours to finish it.

06:35.264 --> 06:36.744
- You were close
with Officer Clark?

06:36.787 --> 06:38.310
[soft dramatic music]

06:38.354 --> 06:41.531
- I don't know about close,
but we moved in a year ago.

06:41.575 --> 06:43.577
He was super friendly,

06:43.620 --> 06:46.841
plus we liked having a cop
in the neighborhood.

06:46.884 --> 06:49.583
Made us feel safe.
- Perfect neighbor.

06:49.626 --> 06:52.412
- He talk about problemsat work or with other cops?

06:52.455 --> 06:54.892
- No, we talked
about positive things

06:54.936 --> 06:55.937
like raising kids.

06:55.980 --> 06:57.721
He wanted a family.

06:57.765 --> 06:59.375
- Did he have someoneto have it with?

06:59.419 --> 07:03.640
- Elise, his girlfriend
from Newark.

07:03.684 --> 07:06.513
I don't have a last name,
but I have a photo.

07:06.556 --> 07:07.601
He sent it to me to show Amna.

07:07.644 --> 07:09.124
♪

07:09.167 --> 07:10.299
He said they were waiting

07:10.342 --> 07:12.432
for the right time
to get married.

07:12.475 --> 07:14.999
♪

07:15.043 --> 07:18.220
- The right time--
how about never?

07:18.263 --> 07:21.092
I broke up with him
four years ago

07:21.136 --> 07:23.660
when he was a cadet
at the Newark Police Academy.

07:23.704 --> 07:25.053
- What happened?

07:25.096 --> 07:26.794
- His moods were too hard
to deal with.

07:26.837 --> 07:28.448
- Give us an example.

07:28.491 --> 07:30.667
- Well, it seems petty,

07:30.711 --> 07:33.801
but we were drivingback from dinner.

07:33.844 --> 07:35.933
We were arguingabout the tip--

07:35.977 --> 07:37.805
Gabe wasn't muchof a tipper--

07:37.848 --> 07:40.111
and he got pulled overfor speeding.

07:40.155 --> 07:41.939
Gabe told the cophe was in the academy,

07:41.983 --> 07:42.897
but the copdidn't care.

07:42.940 --> 07:44.594
- He wrote him up anyway?

07:44.638 --> 07:45.726
- Gabe was furious.

07:45.769 --> 07:47.292
He wouldn't admitthat he was speeding,

07:47.336 --> 07:49.556
but he blamed mefor getting him mad

07:49.599 --> 07:50.992
and makinghim drive too fast.

07:51.035 --> 07:53.603
That was the end of it for me.

07:53.647 --> 07:55.649
- Interesting contradictions--
in Morristown,

07:55.692 --> 07:58.173
he's known for giving out
a lot of traffic tickets.

07:58.216 --> 08:00.349
One law for him,
one law for everybody else.

08:00.392 --> 08:02.003
- But that was four years ago.

08:02.046 --> 08:03.439
He's still telling people
you're his girlfriend.

08:03.483 --> 08:05.485
- Oh, my God.

08:05.528 --> 08:08.531
I mean, about six months
after we broke up,

08:08.575 --> 08:11.012
I let him convince me to give
him a second chance,

08:11.055 --> 08:12.230
but it never clicked.

08:12.274 --> 08:14.711
Then, one day,he called me out of the blue.

08:14.755 --> 08:16.713
He was taking a jobin Morristown.

08:16.757 --> 08:19.063
He asked me to go with him.

08:19.107 --> 08:21.544
I told himI had just gotten engaged.

08:21.588 --> 08:22.806
He begged me to reconsider.

08:22.850 --> 08:25.156
He said he was readyto start a family with me.

08:25.200 --> 08:29.596
I mean, Morristown with Gabe--
I told him no.

08:29.639 --> 08:31.423
[baby crying]

08:31.467 --> 08:33.425
She's awake.

08:35.384 --> 08:36.690
Excuse me.

08:36.733 --> 08:39.693
♪

08:39.736 --> 08:43.087
- Newark Police fired him.
His girlfriend dumped him.

08:43.131 --> 08:45.220
He lost his chanceof having a family.

08:45.263 --> 08:48.136
And two years later,he kills a young trooper

08:48.179 --> 08:49.920
who's about to start a family.

08:49.964 --> 08:51.661
I don't knowif the two are connected,

08:51.705 --> 08:52.836
but they certainly rhyme.

08:52.880 --> 08:55.970
♪

08:56.013 --> 08:57.319
[foreboding music]

08:57.362 --> 08:59.364
- What you got there,young man?

08:59.408 --> 09:01.541
It's okay,
you're not in any trouble.

09:01.584 --> 09:02.716
- Walnuts.

09:02.759 --> 09:04.979
- Salted?
- No.

09:05.022 --> 09:05.980
- Good job.

09:06.023 --> 09:07.677
♪

09:07.721 --> 09:10.637
It's getting late.
You should head home.

09:10.680 --> 09:11.942
Go on.

09:11.986 --> 09:13.901
[police radio chatter]

09:13.944 --> 09:18.470
♪

09:18.514 --> 09:20.603
- Paterson Police Department.

09:20.647 --> 09:22.649
- Hi, I don't know
if it's an emergency.

09:22.692 --> 09:25.347
I probably sound like
an overprotective parent,

09:25.390 --> 09:27.654
but there's a homeless guy
harassing a kid

09:27.697 --> 09:30.439
in Pennington Park
near the pavilion.

09:30.482 --> 09:33.050
- Okay, we'll send someone
to investigate.

09:33.094 --> 09:40.231
♪

09:41.102 --> 09:43.974
- Sir.

09:44.018 --> 09:46.455
Sir, I'm gonna need you
to move along.

09:46.498 --> 09:47.630
♪

09:47.674 --> 09:48.631
[gunshot]

09:48.675 --> 09:50.546
- Head shot, point blank.

09:50.590 --> 09:54.115
Officer Amy Campbell,
three years on the Paterson PD.

09:54.158 --> 09:55.638
She has two kids at home.

09:55.682 --> 09:57.727
- She was respondingto a call about a vagrant.

09:57.771 --> 10:00.034
Came in to the department'snon-emergency line.

10:00.077 --> 10:01.949
Calls aren't recordedor traced.

10:01.992 --> 10:04.168
Number goes back to a burner--this one.

10:04.212 --> 10:06.910
It was foundin that trash can over there.

10:06.954 --> 10:09.826
- Wit saw a cop in the park
at the time of the call.

10:09.870 --> 10:12.176
They picked Clarkout of a six-pack.

10:12.220 --> 10:13.700
- Clark laid a trap.

10:13.743 --> 10:14.918
- Nobody heard the shot.

10:14.962 --> 10:16.659
Couple of witnesses
saw a vagrant

10:16.703 --> 10:19.357
heading out of the park
in no hurry like a Sunday walk.

10:19.401 --> 10:20.881
- He did everything right--

10:20.924 --> 10:24.667
secluded area, dinnertime
so the park was mostly empty,

10:24.711 --> 10:28.497
and a disguise that nobody
would pay attention to.

10:28.540 --> 10:30.238
He put a lot of effort
into this.

10:30.281 --> 10:32.980
- You guys have to see this.
It's trending on Reddit.

10:33.023 --> 10:36.070
♪

10:36.113 --> 10:38.376
- My name
is Officer Gabriel Clark

10:38.420 --> 10:39.682
of the Morristown
Police Department.

10:39.726 --> 10:42.685
I have a short statement
to make.

10:42.729 --> 10:46.776
We live in a world of lies--
fake news, fake facts,

10:46.820 --> 10:48.517
dirty things
made to look clean,

10:48.560 --> 10:50.693
phony pictures,
leaders telling us up is down,

10:50.737 --> 10:53.000
and everywhere, people
who are breaking their word.

10:53.043 --> 10:56.394
Truth--the most important
thing in life is the truth.

10:56.438 --> 11:00.311
Now, I've always told
the truth, but they haven't.

11:00.355 --> 11:03.314
I regret
I have taken lives,

11:03.358 --> 11:05.490
and I regret
I'll have to take more lives

11:05.534 --> 11:06.840
until they tell the truth.

11:06.883 --> 11:08.624
♪

11:08.668 --> 11:10.757
- Well, now,
that's a declaration of war.

11:10.800 --> 11:12.672
♪

11:20.288 --> 11:22.594
- It's the metadata
from Clark's video.

11:22.638 --> 11:25.554
He uploaded it the morningbefore he killed the troopers

11:25.597 --> 11:26.729
and scheduled its release

11:26.773 --> 11:29.427
for todayafter he killed Campbell.

11:29.471 --> 11:31.473
- He has every step
planned out.

11:31.516 --> 11:34.258
- Campbell was with Newark PD
before she joined Paterson.

11:34.302 --> 11:36.739
She quit Newark six monthsbefore Clark did.

11:36.783 --> 11:37.871
- They served there
at the same time.

11:37.914 --> 11:39.394
Doesn't mean he targeted her.

11:39.437 --> 11:41.222
- But if he knewher patrol schedule,

11:41.265 --> 11:43.964
he'd know she'd be the oneto respond to the call.

11:44.007 --> 11:46.183
- All he'd need
is a police scanner.

11:46.227 --> 11:47.968
- Let's go
back over the troopers.

11:48.011 --> 11:49.752
Look for any connection
to Newark.

11:49.796 --> 11:53.538
And I want everything
on Clark's stint in Newark.

11:53.582 --> 11:56.454
- I regret
I have taken lives,

11:56.498 --> 11:58.805
and I regret
I'll have to take more lives

11:58.848 --> 11:59.980
until they tell the truth.

12:00.023 --> 12:01.808
- The truth, the truth--I don't know

12:01.851 --> 12:03.331
what this has to do with us.

12:03.374 --> 12:06.813
We gave the guy a fair shake.Not everybody makes the cut.

12:06.856 --> 12:08.162
- Your probation report
was thin

12:08.205 --> 12:09.337
on the reasons he left.

12:09.380 --> 12:11.165
- I didn't wannasubmarine his chances

12:11.208 --> 12:13.167
of getting another job.

12:13.210 --> 12:16.518
Clark was rigid, argumentative,everything's black and white.

12:16.561 --> 12:18.476
You can't do the jobwith that attitude.

12:18.520 --> 12:20.348
- Better to bend
so you don't break.

12:20.391 --> 12:21.871
- Right.

12:21.915 --> 12:25.092
- What was Clark's relationship
with Officer Campbell?

12:25.135 --> 12:27.964
- Just a fellow officer.
They didn't patrol together.

12:28.008 --> 12:29.400
Amy was a pro.

12:29.444 --> 12:31.794
- But she left
around the same time Clark did.

12:31.838 --> 12:33.361
- Paterson made hera better offer--

12:33.404 --> 12:35.842
more benefits,more time with her kids.

12:35.885 --> 12:38.148
She just had the rotten luck ofgetting in that bastard's way.

12:38.192 --> 12:40.107
- We're not so sure luck
had anything to do with it.

12:40.150 --> 12:41.630
They worked
in the same precinct in Newark.

12:41.673 --> 12:44.459
- Yeah, well,with 200 other police officers.

12:49.986 --> 12:53.468
I don't knowwhat else I can tell you.

12:53.511 --> 12:54.991
- Thanks for your time,Lieutenant.

12:55.035 --> 12:56.993
[phone rings]

12:57.037 --> 12:58.560
- Yeah?

12:58.603 --> 13:00.605
- Lieutenant Peroniseems a little too happy

13:00.649 --> 13:02.694
to kick his problemdown the road to Morristown.

13:02.738 --> 13:04.392
- It would've been nice
if he put a couple red flags

13:04.435 --> 13:06.742
in the probation report.
[phone chimes]

13:06.786 --> 13:08.222
Text from Hana:

13:08.265 --> 13:11.355
"Trooper Kubiak's fatheris a paramedic in Newark--

13:11.399 --> 13:13.053
specifically,right in this precinct."

13:13.096 --> 13:16.056
[dramatic music]

13:16.099 --> 13:17.187
♪

13:17.231 --> 13:18.885
- All I know
about Gabriel Clark

13:18.928 --> 13:20.887
is that he killed my son.

13:20.930 --> 13:22.062
The sooner you catch him

13:22.105 --> 13:24.238
and send him to hell,
the better.

13:24.281 --> 13:27.589
- We'll do just that
with your help.

13:27.632 --> 13:29.156
Clark grew up in Newark.

13:29.199 --> 13:30.984
Is there any chance
your son knew him?

13:32.724 --> 13:34.248
- I don't see how.

13:34.291 --> 13:36.685
Tyler grew up in Edison
with his mother.

13:36.728 --> 13:37.947
- Maybe when he visited you?

13:37.991 --> 13:39.296
- No, Tyler's a mellow kid.

13:39.340 --> 13:40.863
He wouldn't be hanging
with a guy like Clark.

13:40.907 --> 13:42.212
- Like Clark?

13:42.256 --> 13:44.214
- Yeah, you know, a hard-ass.

13:45.389 --> 13:47.217
- Maybe you ran into Clark,
Mr. Kubiak.

13:47.261 --> 13:49.393
You work in his old precinct.

13:50.830 --> 13:52.353
- Take a good look at him.

13:54.529 --> 13:56.444
- Never seen him.

13:56.487 --> 13:58.794
Makes me sick
just to even look at him.

13:58.838 --> 14:00.100
- I understand.

14:00.143 --> 14:01.318
For a guy you never met,

14:01.362 --> 14:04.060
you pretty much nailed him
with hard-ass.

14:05.757 --> 14:08.891
- Mr. Kubiak, we think
there is a personal reason

14:08.935 --> 14:10.240
Clark targeted your son.

14:10.284 --> 14:13.200
[solemn music]

14:13.243 --> 14:15.898
♪

14:15.942 --> 14:17.160
- It wasn't about Tyler.

14:17.204 --> 14:19.162
♪

14:19.206 --> 14:20.816
It was about me.

14:20.860 --> 14:23.993
♪

14:24.037 --> 14:27.040
Three years ago,
I got called to a shooting

14:27.083 --> 14:29.390
involving the Newark PD.

14:29.433 --> 14:31.218
It was a drug raid on a house.

14:31.261 --> 14:33.524
A civilian inside the house
was shot by the police.

14:33.568 --> 14:35.831
- Clark was part
of the raid team?

14:35.875 --> 14:40.488
- Yeah, I saw Clark arguing
with another cop--female cop.

14:40.531 --> 14:44.187
He said, "They did it wrong.
They didn't ID themselves."

14:44.231 --> 14:45.797
- They who?
The other police officers?

14:45.841 --> 14:47.190
- Yeah, I think so.

14:47.234 --> 14:49.323
Looked like the other cops
were upset with Clark.

14:49.366 --> 14:51.673
Two weeks later,
my boss tells me

14:51.716 --> 14:56.286
that the Newark PD
is investigating the shooting

14:56.330 --> 14:57.635
and that I'm
gonna be interviewed.

14:57.679 --> 14:59.333
♪

14:59.376 --> 15:02.075
So he told me,
"This is the PD circus.

15:02.118 --> 15:05.469
The less you remember,
the better."

15:05.513 --> 15:06.949
- And what
did he tell you to forget?

15:06.993 --> 15:09.952
- That I overheard Clark
arguing with the other cops.

15:09.996 --> 15:12.868
♪

15:12.912 --> 15:15.349
So I lied.

15:15.392 --> 15:17.090
I told their investigators
that...

15:17.133 --> 15:20.441
[sighs]
I didn't hear a thing.

15:20.484 --> 15:23.661
- Which probably contradicted
what Clark said.

15:23.705 --> 15:26.795
A few months later,
he got fired.

15:26.838 --> 15:29.798
- Why didn't he come after me?
Tyler didn't do a thing.

15:29.841 --> 15:36.761
♪

15:38.067 --> 15:39.939
- Clark probably
killed Kubiak first

15:39.982 --> 15:42.158
so no one would guess
what his game plan was.

15:42.202 --> 15:43.986
- Not to mentionthere's no worse punishment

15:44.030 --> 15:45.031
than losing your child.

15:45.074 --> 15:46.641
♪

15:46.684 --> 15:48.556
- That's not
why Clark got fired.

15:48.599 --> 15:51.037
- Did Amy Campbell
participate in the raid?

15:51.080 --> 15:52.821
- Yes, there werea dozen police officers,

15:52.864 --> 15:54.170
but I'm telling you
the raid had nothing

15:54.214 --> 15:55.606
to do with Clark getting fired.

15:55.650 --> 15:58.044
- Clark seems to think it does.

15:58.087 --> 15:59.523
It's what's driving
these killings.

15:59.567 --> 16:01.134
Could you tell us
what happened?

16:01.177 --> 16:02.962
- Narco got a tip
from a CI about a meth lab

16:03.005 --> 16:04.964
operating out of a house
in the Ironbound District.

16:05.007 --> 16:07.053
Team serveda no-knock warrant,

16:07.096 --> 16:08.271
the occupant pulled a gun,we opened fire,

16:08.315 --> 16:09.316
and the guy died.

16:09.359 --> 16:10.926
Drugs were found, no meth lab.

16:10.970 --> 16:13.711
- Clark was upset the officers
didn't identify themselves?

16:13.755 --> 16:16.018
- Clark just didn't hearthe ID, but everyone else did.

16:16.062 --> 16:17.977
That's whatthe investigation showed.

16:18.020 --> 16:19.239
- We need the reporton the raid

16:19.282 --> 16:20.849
and the namesof everyone involved.

16:20.892 --> 16:24.200
- Why, so you can waste your
time interviewing them again?

16:24.244 --> 16:27.073
- So we can protect them
and their families.

16:27.116 --> 16:29.162
They're targets now.

16:29.205 --> 16:31.033
- Then you better put a detailon my family

16:31.077 --> 16:32.774
'cause I signed offon the raid.

16:38.519 --> 16:41.870
[suspenseful music]

16:41.913 --> 16:48.877
♪

16:48.920 --> 16:49.878
- There he is!

16:49.921 --> 16:51.271
[gunshots]

16:51.314 --> 16:52.794
- He's on the move!

16:52.837 --> 16:55.840
Circle around
the other side! Go!

16:55.884 --> 16:56.972
[car beeps]

16:57.016 --> 17:03.979
♪

17:04.023 --> 17:06.286
[tires squealing]

17:08.244 --> 17:09.985
- [grunting]

17:10.029 --> 17:12.988
- The dead man's widow saidthe cops didn't ID themselves.

17:13.032 --> 17:14.381
Her husband thought
it was a home invasion,

17:14.424 --> 17:15.686
pulled out a gun.

17:15.730 --> 17:17.732
The drugs the cops foundwere 1/2 ounce of weed.

17:17.775 --> 17:19.342
- Their investigation
isn't much--

17:19.386 --> 17:22.693
statements contradicting Clark,
a couple of field reports.

17:22.737 --> 17:24.826
Looks like they were in a rushto bury Clark's complaint.

17:24.869 --> 17:26.915
- Security cameras
two blocks away

17:26.958 --> 17:28.699
caught Clark driving away.

17:30.310 --> 17:33.095
- The cops guarding the house
threw 20-plus bullets his way.

17:33.139 --> 17:34.314
No sign that they hit him.

17:34.357 --> 17:35.837
- Twenty shots?Who started the shooting?

17:35.880 --> 17:36.881
- Cops.

17:36.925 --> 17:38.970
No evidence
Clark returned fire.

17:39.014 --> 17:40.276
- If I didn't know better,

17:40.320 --> 17:41.886
it'd look like they got ordersto shoot on sight.

17:44.237 --> 17:46.587
- I found something.
Look at this.

17:46.630 --> 17:48.850
It's from
the police dispatch records.

17:48.893 --> 17:51.026
Right before Frank Kubiak,
the paramedic,

17:51.070 --> 17:54.334
was dispatched to the raid
here at 484 South Drummond,

17:54.377 --> 17:56.031
another ambulance
was dispatched

17:56.075 --> 17:59.382
to 484 North Drummond here.
That call was canceled.

17:59.426 --> 18:00.731
- That ambulance went
to the wrong address.

18:00.775 --> 18:02.820
Happens all the time
with North/South streets.

18:02.864 --> 18:04.953
- Cops raided the house
on South Drummond

18:04.996 --> 18:08.261
hoping to find a meth lab,
found nothing.

18:08.304 --> 18:10.741
I wonder
what's on North Drummond.

18:10.785 --> 18:12.439
- Looks like a fire
hit the place.

18:12.482 --> 18:14.484
[soft dramatic music]

18:14.528 --> 18:17.052
- Excuse me, ma'am.Sorry to bother you.

18:17.096 --> 18:18.532
My friends and I are wondering
what happened

18:18.575 --> 18:19.707
to that house next door.

18:19.750 --> 18:21.361
- That house blew up
two years ago.

18:21.404 --> 18:22.362
They were cooking drugs
in the basement.

18:22.405 --> 18:25.191
- That's just terrible.Thank you.

18:25.234 --> 18:27.106
This is where the meth lab was.

18:27.149 --> 18:29.151
- The first ambulancewas sent here.

18:29.195 --> 18:30.587
The dispatcher would've usedthe address

18:30.631 --> 18:32.502
in the operations plan--the actual address

18:32.546 --> 18:34.025
Newark PD got from the tip.

18:34.069 --> 18:37.159
- The ambulance got here,didn't find a raid in progress,

18:37.203 --> 18:38.552
so the call was canceled.

18:38.595 --> 18:41.207
- The second ambulance was sentto where the raid was

18:41.250 --> 18:43.557
on South Drummond.

18:43.600 --> 18:45.080
- Cops went
to the wrong address.

18:45.124 --> 18:49.432
♪

18:49.476 --> 18:51.130
We need to talk to you alone.

18:51.173 --> 18:58.267
♪

19:07.015 --> 19:08.364
- What can I do for you?

19:08.408 --> 19:10.279
- You can start
by telling the truth.

19:10.323 --> 19:13.239
You raided the wrong house
three years ago.

19:13.282 --> 19:14.588
- Now, you wait a minute.

19:14.631 --> 19:16.372
- Your mistake cost
an innocent man his life.

19:16.416 --> 19:18.635
That's why you deep-sixed
Clark's complaint.

19:18.679 --> 19:20.942
Too much digging around
would've shown up your mistake.

19:20.985 --> 19:22.378
- You don't knowwhat you're talking about.

19:22.422 --> 19:23.640
- I know this--

19:23.684 --> 19:25.512
you impeded
an FBI investigation

19:25.555 --> 19:27.340
and put people's lives at risk!

19:27.383 --> 19:29.820
Clark kills anybody else,
it's on you!

19:29.864 --> 19:35.522
♪

19:40.831 --> 19:42.398
- The FBI's
initial investigation

19:42.442 --> 19:43.965
found evidence
that the Newark Police

19:44.008 --> 19:46.054
raided the wrong address
resulting in the death

19:46.097 --> 19:48.665
of the homeowner along
with evidence of a cover-up

19:48.709 --> 19:50.754
by supervisory officers.

19:50.798 --> 19:53.192
As a result,
the FBI will conduct

19:53.235 --> 19:55.672
a full investigation into
the Newark Police Department's

19:55.716 --> 19:57.848
handling
of the Ironbound raid.

19:57.892 --> 20:00.242
I'll now turn this over
to Special Agent Jess LaCroix

20:00.286 --> 20:02.636
who conducted
the initial investigation.

20:02.679 --> 20:03.680
Jess.

20:03.724 --> 20:06.683
[soft dramatic music]

20:06.727 --> 20:07.684
♪

20:07.728 --> 20:08.859
- I'm addressing myself

20:08.903 --> 20:12.733
to former police officer
Gabriel Clark.

20:12.776 --> 20:14.952
Mr. Clark, I understand
nobody listened

20:14.996 --> 20:16.432
when you said
the Newark Police Department

20:16.476 --> 20:19.566
was hiding something.

20:19.609 --> 20:22.046
Nobody listened
when you said they lied.

20:22.090 --> 20:23.918
♪

20:23.961 --> 20:25.528
Well,
everybody's listening now.

20:25.572 --> 20:27.922
♪

20:27.965 --> 20:30.533
We will find the truth,

20:30.577 --> 20:32.709
but I need you
to turn yourself in.

20:32.753 --> 20:36.147
I need your testimony
to make it right.

20:36.191 --> 20:38.237
♪

20:38.280 --> 20:41.065
Please call me.

20:41.109 --> 20:43.242
- The investigation's big news.

20:43.285 --> 20:44.591
- Trending heavily.

20:44.634 --> 20:46.114
- Editorials are piling on:

20:46.157 --> 20:48.725
"Are Vigilante Deaths
the Price of Police Deception?"

20:48.769 --> 20:50.074
- Isn't this adorable?

20:50.118 --> 20:52.381
Someone's crowdfunding
for Clark's defense.

20:52.425 --> 20:54.644
- If it convinces him
to surrender, I'll take it.

20:54.688 --> 20:57.212
- Think I found
what triggered Clark.

20:57.256 --> 20:59.562
The family of the homeowner
who got killed?

20:59.606 --> 21:01.303
Their lawsuit got dismissed

21:01.347 --> 21:04.132
a week before Clark
killed those troopers.

21:04.175 --> 21:06.177
[phone rings]

21:06.221 --> 21:09.224
- Crosby.
It's him.

21:09.268 --> 21:12.271
Yeah, put him through.

21:19.321 --> 21:22.063
- This is Agent LaCroix.
Who am I speaking to?

21:22.106 --> 21:23.369
- Officer Clark.

21:23.412 --> 21:25.936
Good job turning over the rock,
Agent LaCroix.

21:25.980 --> 21:28.025
Wrong address,
that was a new one on me.

21:28.069 --> 21:30.158
- It won't add up to anything
without your testimony.

21:30.201 --> 21:32.029
- Well, you got more faith
in the system than I do.

21:32.073 --> 21:33.727
Listen,
I have a message for you.

21:33.770 --> 21:36.382
Stop looking for me.

21:36.425 --> 21:37.861
- You know I can't do that,

21:37.905 --> 21:39.210
but I'll do everything I can
to make sure

21:39.254 --> 21:41.517
you get a fair hearing,
and I can promise you

21:41.561 --> 21:43.780
the satisfaction of seeing
the people who wronged you

21:43.824 --> 21:45.478
pay for their crimes.

21:45.521 --> 21:47.306
- I'm not that naive.

21:47.349 --> 21:49.612
You're promising things
that you can't deliver.

21:49.656 --> 21:52.267
In your own way,
you're corrupt.

21:52.311 --> 21:53.486
I like my way better.

21:53.529 --> 21:55.314
- You mean killing people?

21:55.357 --> 21:57.054
- It's more honest.
It's straightforward.

21:57.098 --> 21:59.840
- Truthful--the truth
is important to you, right?

21:59.883 --> 22:01.015
- The further away
you get from it,

22:01.058 --> 22:02.930
the more complicated
things get.

22:02.973 --> 22:06.542
Things are simple if you're
pure, good, and serious,

22:06.586 --> 22:08.283
a friend of justice,

22:08.327 --> 22:10.459
and resolute
in your devotion to duty.

22:10.503 --> 22:12.461
♪

22:12.505 --> 22:13.854
- I know those words.

22:13.897 --> 22:16.378
He also said,
"The best revenge is

22:16.422 --> 22:18.728
to be unlike
those who injured you."

22:18.772 --> 22:20.861
♪

22:20.904 --> 22:22.645
People are more likely
to quote the Kardashians

22:22.689 --> 22:23.994
than Roman philosophers.

22:24.038 --> 22:26.083
How'd you come
across Marcus Aurelius?

22:26.127 --> 22:28.347
- I had a good coach.
We're done here.

22:28.390 --> 22:31.480
- Gabriel, wait, let's keep
the line of communication open.

22:31.524 --> 22:33.134
- There's nothing
I want from you.

22:33.177 --> 22:35.397
- How about a front row seat
to the Ironbound investigation?

22:35.441 --> 22:37.399
I'll tell you what I know
when I know it.

22:37.443 --> 22:39.662
You can watch the heads roll.

22:39.706 --> 22:42.099
Fine, but it won't stop me.

22:42.143 --> 22:44.363
- One step at a time.

22:44.406 --> 22:46.539
I need a way
to get in touch with you.

22:46.582 --> 22:47.975
[foreboding music]

22:48.018 --> 22:50.151
You like sudoku, right?

22:50.194 --> 22:53.850
You know the site SudokuStorm?

22:53.894 --> 22:56.113
- Sure.
- There's a message board.

22:56.157 --> 22:58.464
When I have news, I'll post
under Jessie Williams.

22:58.507 --> 23:01.423
You can call me.

23:01.467 --> 23:03.077
[sighs]

23:04.513 --> 23:05.688
- Got the burner number,

23:05.732 --> 23:07.081
but I couldn't get
the location.

23:07.124 --> 23:09.562
Good news is, we can tracewhere he bought the phone.

23:09.605 --> 23:12.042
[soft dramatic music]

23:12.086 --> 23:14.610
- Four phones, huh?

23:14.654 --> 23:18.440
What would I do...
with four phones?

23:18.484 --> 23:20.703
Only got my two hands.

23:20.747 --> 23:22.183
- Mr. Clark, we have video

23:22.226 --> 23:23.532
of you buyingfour burner phones

23:23.576 --> 23:26.100
at a store on West Mainthree days before your son

23:26.143 --> 23:27.884
killed two state troopers.

23:27.928 --> 23:29.190
- Are you sure it's me?

23:29.233 --> 23:32.280
'Cause I got a faceGod handed out like candy.

23:32.323 --> 23:34.413
- You're a clever fellow,Mr. Clark,

23:34.456 --> 23:37.024
dodging our questions.

23:37.067 --> 23:39.287
- Hey, I just
don't wanna lie to the FBI.

23:41.115 --> 23:42.986
- Well, look at this.
What we got here?

23:43.030 --> 23:44.988
- Eh, nah, nah, nah,
you give me that, huh?

23:45.032 --> 23:47.513
- This is, what?
At least 100 bucks.

23:47.556 --> 23:49.210
Haven't even opened it yet.

23:49.253 --> 23:50.429
- Did Gabrielgive you that

23:50.472 --> 23:51.734
for running that errandto the phone store?

23:51.778 --> 23:53.997
- My son loves me.

23:54.041 --> 23:56.783
He gave me that
'cause he's going away.

23:57.958 --> 23:59.568
- Going away
with his buddy Marcus?

23:59.612 --> 24:00.830
- Who?

24:00.874 --> 24:02.963
- Marcus Aurelius.

24:03.006 --> 24:06.270
- That's a screwy name.I never heard of him.

24:07.533 --> 24:09.491
- I'm sure you haven't,
Mr. Clark.

24:09.535 --> 24:11.058
You take care of that bottle.

24:18.021 --> 24:19.893
- There wasn'ta single bottle of alcohol

24:19.936 --> 24:21.285
at Gabriel Clark's house.

24:21.329 --> 24:23.505
- He's one apple
that fell as far away

24:23.549 --> 24:24.463
from the tree as possible.

24:25.899 --> 24:27.030
- Thank you.

24:27.074 --> 24:28.292
- I know Clark's
an extreme example,

24:28.336 --> 24:30.077
but even with
my daughter, Anais,

24:30.120 --> 24:32.296
I wonder what unintendedlessons she's learning from me.

24:32.340 --> 24:33.950
- Probably, no matter what
you do as a parent,

24:33.994 --> 24:35.169
you never really know

24:35.212 --> 24:36.823
what your kid's
gonna turn out like.

24:36.866 --> 24:38.215
I'm going through
that with Tali.

24:38.259 --> 24:40.391
- My mom told me
you grounded her.

24:40.435 --> 24:42.176
- Yeah, she wandered off
without telling anyone

24:42.219 --> 24:44.308
and turned her phone off.

24:44.352 --> 24:46.049
- Aren't you the guy
who told us

24:46.093 --> 24:48.225
when to hold the line
and when to give a little?

24:48.269 --> 24:49.792
- I guess I'm that guy.

24:49.836 --> 24:52.099
- Yeah, you're that guy,
but now you don't have Angelyne

24:52.142 --> 24:53.230
to straighten you out

24:59.019 --> 25:01.325
- That coach Clark mentioned,

25:01.369 --> 25:03.632
I wonder if he might still
have an influence on him.

25:03.676 --> 25:07.244
- Maybe, if he's still around
and we can find him.

25:11.814 --> 25:14.991
- Truth before all--a motto, but for what?

25:15.035 --> 25:16.602
- I ran it
through the database.

25:16.645 --> 25:17.820
Goose eggs.

25:17.864 --> 25:19.213
- Maybe some kind
of law enforcement?

25:19.256 --> 25:20.780
A cop gave it to him?

25:20.823 --> 25:22.216
- But which cop?

25:22.259 --> 25:24.348
- When Newark investigated
Clark's claim

25:24.392 --> 25:26.002
the police didn'tidentify themselves.

25:26.046 --> 25:29.571
A lot of witnessescalled him a liar.

25:29.615 --> 25:31.051
Did anybody support him?

25:31.094 --> 25:32.705
♪

25:32.748 --> 25:35.359
- I wrote a letterof support for Gabe.

25:35.403 --> 25:37.318
I wish I could've testifiedin person,

25:37.361 --> 25:39.363
but my wife, Susan,was going through chemo,

25:39.407 --> 25:41.583
and I just couldn't takethe time off.

25:41.627 --> 25:42.845
- Still, the testimony

25:42.889 --> 25:44.847
of a former police sergeant
meant something.

25:44.891 --> 25:47.633
- Hm, not enough.

25:47.676 --> 25:50.374
If I could've made the case
for him in person, you know,

25:50.418 --> 25:53.029
convinced those people
what a decent kid he was,

25:53.073 --> 25:54.901
I mean, none of this
would have happened.

25:56.555 --> 25:58.121
- You taught him this?

25:58.165 --> 26:00.341
- My old Sam Brown belt buckle.

26:00.384 --> 26:02.386
I gave this to him
when he turned 16

26:02.430 --> 26:05.041
to remind him to work hard
and be truthful.

26:06.303 --> 26:08.218
- He called you his coach.
Is that how you met?

26:08.262 --> 26:09.611
He played for you?
- No.

26:09.655 --> 26:11.047
We lived down the street
from where he grew up.

26:11.091 --> 26:12.440
Please, sit.
Sit down.

26:14.224 --> 26:15.661
I was the cop next door.

26:15.704 --> 26:17.924
A lot of people came to me
with their problems.

26:17.967 --> 26:19.839
One day, I was working
on my car,

26:19.882 --> 26:21.405
and this little kid
walks up,

26:21.449 --> 26:23.494
says he's running away
and can I help him.

26:23.538 --> 26:25.932
- Running away?
Yeah, we met his father.

26:25.975 --> 26:27.281
- Then you know.

26:27.324 --> 26:28.499
Gabe's mom had just died,

26:28.543 --> 26:31.241
and Ted couldn't see
past his own sorry self.

26:31.285 --> 26:32.852
We let Gabe stay the night.

26:32.895 --> 26:35.245
We have two older girls,
and they just spoiled Gabe.

26:35.289 --> 26:36.595
After that,
he came by

26:36.638 --> 26:39.772
every other day or so
and followed me around.

26:39.815 --> 26:41.556
- Like a son.

26:41.600 --> 26:43.123
- Something like that.

26:43.166 --> 26:45.429
It was nice
to teach him things.

26:45.473 --> 26:46.692
- You taught himabout the truth?

26:46.735 --> 26:48.519
- Taught him
it's the most important thing.

26:51.305 --> 26:53.873
You know,
I should have noticed.

26:53.916 --> 26:55.483
Even as a kid,
Gabe couldn't relax.

26:55.526 --> 26:58.573
It was all or nothing with him.

26:58.617 --> 27:00.793
Time wears away
most people's sharp edges--

27:00.836 --> 27:02.577
not Gabe.

27:02.621 --> 27:04.971
I should've made more
of an effort to reach out,

27:05.014 --> 27:06.929
but Susan was dying,
and I just...

27:06.973 --> 27:09.932
[solemn music]

27:09.976 --> 27:10.977
♪

27:11.020 --> 27:12.195
- Mr. Higgins,you might be

27:12.239 --> 27:14.110
the only personhe'd listen to right now.

27:14.154 --> 27:17.287
We need to stop him.We need to bring him in.

27:17.331 --> 27:18.767
Would you be willing to try?

27:18.811 --> 27:22.031
♪

27:22.075 --> 27:25.600
[gun clicking]

27:25.644 --> 27:27.820
[phone chimes]

27:27.863 --> 27:30.823
[tense music]

27:30.866 --> 27:37.786
♪

27:37.830 --> 27:39.309
[phone rings]

27:39.353 --> 27:40.789
- Burner phone.
It's him.

27:40.833 --> 27:43.226
♪

27:43.270 --> 27:44.924
- You're on, Mr. Higgins.

27:44.967 --> 27:49.319
♪

27:49.363 --> 27:50.364
- Hello?

27:50.407 --> 27:52.018
- Ray, I got a message
to call you.

27:52.061 --> 27:54.368
- Gabe, thank you for calling.

27:54.411 --> 27:56.805
I'm so glad to hear your voice.

27:56.849 --> 27:57.980
- I didn't call you before

27:58.024 --> 27:59.765
because I wanted
to keep you out of this,

27:59.808 --> 28:03.159
but if anyone can understand
what I'm doing, you can.

28:03.203 --> 28:05.684
- Gabe, I know it comes
from a good place,

28:05.727 --> 28:09.513
but it's not right.
I don't wanna see you hurt.

28:09.557 --> 28:13.082
I couldn't take that.
Please, Gabe, stop all this.

28:13.126 --> 28:14.344
Turn yourself in.

28:14.388 --> 28:15.694
- Don't you see
what they did to me?

28:15.737 --> 28:18.392
They lied to me.
They lied about everything.

28:18.435 --> 28:21.482
- Truth is important, but you
are taking this too far.

28:21.525 --> 28:24.485
- No, they took it too far.
They ruined me.

28:24.528 --> 28:25.791
They ruined it with Elise.

28:25.834 --> 28:28.010
They ruined my chance
of having a family.

28:28.054 --> 28:31.535
- Please, Gabe--I talked
to Agent LaCroix.

28:31.579 --> 28:33.189
He said
if you turn yourself in--

28:33.233 --> 28:34.887
- Agent LaCroix?

28:34.930 --> 28:37.150
He says,
"Bend so you don't break."

28:37.193 --> 28:39.630
♪

28:39.674 --> 28:41.371
But you keep bending,
and one day,

28:41.415 --> 28:43.286
everything that you believe in,

28:43.330 --> 28:45.854
everything
you stand for breaks.

28:45.898 --> 28:47.726
♪

28:47.769 --> 28:50.772
You tell Agent LaCroix
he can't protect everyone.

28:50.816 --> 28:52.556
[phone beeps]

28:52.600 --> 28:53.601
- Gabe.

28:53.644 --> 28:56.125
[dramatic music]

28:56.169 --> 28:58.911
- He hung up.

28:58.954 --> 29:02.218
- Oh, my God.
What have I done?

29:02.262 --> 29:04.090
- It's not your fault,
Mr. Higgins.

29:04.133 --> 29:06.657
- Clark's right.
We can't protect everyone.

29:06.701 --> 29:08.224
- [sighs]

29:08.268 --> 29:10.400
- What he starts, he finishes--
just like that baby crib.

29:10.444 --> 29:11.837
- We have another problem.

29:11.880 --> 29:15.405
Someone inside the Newark PD
is talking to Clark.

29:15.449 --> 29:20.062
"Bend so you don't break."
I never told Clark that.

29:20.106 --> 29:22.151
But I did tell
Lieutenant Peroni.

29:22.195 --> 29:27.417
♪

29:32.640 --> 29:34.773
- "Bend so you don't break."
I told you that,

29:34.816 --> 29:37.427
and Clark repeated it
to me word for word.

29:37.471 --> 29:38.777
Explain that to me.

29:38.820 --> 29:40.735
- Spill it, Peroni.

29:40.779 --> 29:43.216
- I sent an email
after Agent LaCroix left

29:43.259 --> 29:45.174
to Lieutenant DeSantis
in 10th.

29:47.002 --> 29:48.830
- Show them the email.

29:48.874 --> 29:51.354
- It wasn't
exactly complimentary.

29:51.398 --> 29:54.183
- I'll work through it
with my therapist.

29:54.227 --> 29:55.315
Let's see it.

30:01.669 --> 30:04.803
"The feds are bigfooting us.
You'd love the guy they sent.

30:04.846 --> 30:06.543
"He enlightened me
with his FBI wisdom.

30:06.587 --> 30:08.023
"'Bend so you don't break.'

30:08.067 --> 30:10.025
"I'd like to see him bend
with that 2 by 4

30:10.069 --> 30:12.375
he's got stuck
up his butt."

30:12.419 --> 30:15.944
I'd like to see that too.
What about this DeSantis?

30:15.988 --> 30:19.861
- Never worked with Clark.
No relationship there.

30:19.905 --> 30:21.950
- You mind?
- Of course.

30:34.963 --> 30:36.660
[phone beeps]

30:36.704 --> 30:38.227
- You got malware
on your phone.

30:38.271 --> 30:40.229
Clark's been reading
your emails and your texts.

30:40.273 --> 30:41.578
Your computer's
probably infected too.

30:41.622 --> 30:43.972
- That's how he's keeping tabson your department.

30:44.016 --> 30:47.889
♪

30:47.933 --> 30:50.979
- It'll take a minute
to disinfect.

30:51.023 --> 30:53.068
- Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait.

30:53.112 --> 30:54.635
We don't knowwho Clark's next target is.

30:54.678 --> 30:57.420
Maybe we could steer himto a target that we do know.

30:57.464 --> 31:04.384
♪

31:06.821 --> 31:08.344
- What was that?

31:08.388 --> 31:10.694
"Running, Gabriel's
only making it worse."

31:10.738 --> 31:12.609
- What's wrong with that?
- Syntax.

31:12.653 --> 31:14.176
Subject, verb, object?

31:14.220 --> 31:16.787
Running isn't the subject.
Gabriel is the subject.

31:16.831 --> 31:18.920
"Gabriel's making it worse
by running."

31:18.964 --> 31:20.443
Isn't that how you'd say it,
Mr. Higgins?

31:20.487 --> 31:22.271
- Yeah, I guess so.

31:22.315 --> 31:23.751
- Somewhere,
your English teacher

31:23.794 --> 31:25.753
is pumping her fist--
"yeah."

31:25.796 --> 31:27.929
- See?
That was proper syntax.

31:28.974 --> 31:30.279
- I never lied to Gabe.

31:30.323 --> 31:32.281
I don't feel good
about doing it now.

31:32.325 --> 31:35.371
- I understand, Ray, but it'sa lie that might save lives,

31:35.415 --> 31:36.546
including his.

31:36.590 --> 31:38.157
- Okay, I'm done.

31:43.162 --> 31:45.642
- Mm-hmm, it's good.
- Cool?

31:45.686 --> 31:48.558
All right, I just have to add
an email chain.

31:48.602 --> 31:52.258
♪

31:52.301 --> 31:54.913
Good to go.

31:54.956 --> 31:56.784
- Okay.

31:56.827 --> 32:01.354
♪

32:01.397 --> 32:02.877
- Sent.

32:02.921 --> 32:04.661
- Let's hope the fish bites.

32:04.705 --> 32:11.625
♪

32:15.585 --> 32:16.673
[computer chimes]

32:16.717 --> 32:19.676
[dramatic music]

32:19.720 --> 32:24.812
♪

32:24.855 --> 32:27.075
- "As you know,
I had a phone call

32:27.119 --> 32:29.730
"with Gabriel Clark yesterday.
It did not go well.

32:29.773 --> 32:31.862
He's gone off the rails."

32:31.906 --> 32:34.996
"Gone off the rails."
Come on, Ray.

32:35.040 --> 32:37.346
"He's not the young man
I once knew.

32:37.390 --> 32:39.392
"Gabriel's making it worse
by running.

32:39.435 --> 32:42.351
I can only imagine
what he'd do to me if he knew."

32:42.395 --> 32:45.702
"If I knew."
If I knew what, Ray?

32:45.746 --> 32:47.052
What did you do?

32:47.095 --> 32:49.010
♪

32:49.054 --> 32:50.794
"Mr. Higgins, thank you
for agreeing

32:50.838 --> 32:55.147
"not to testify in person
at Officer Clark's hearing.

32:55.190 --> 32:57.236
"The Board understood
that sending a letter

32:57.279 --> 33:00.021
"instead of appearing in person
meant that even you,

33:00.065 --> 33:02.110
"Clark's mentor, didn't support
his version

33:02.154 --> 33:05.766
of what happened
at the Ironbound drug raid."

33:05.809 --> 33:07.463
No!
No!

33:07.507 --> 33:09.552
Ray, you son of a bitch.

33:09.596 --> 33:12.033
♪

33:12.077 --> 33:13.078
[phone rings]

33:13.121 --> 33:17.908
♪

33:17.952 --> 33:20.215
- Hello?
- It's me.

33:20.259 --> 33:22.609
- Are you all right, Gabe?
- No.

33:22.652 --> 33:25.568
This whole thing--
I'm tired.

33:25.612 --> 33:28.876
I thought about what you said
about taking things too far.

33:28.919 --> 33:32.619
I'll surrender, but only
to you--someplace I choose.

33:32.662 --> 33:34.751
Head east on Route 40.
I'll call you.

33:34.795 --> 33:37.841
♪

33:37.885 --> 33:39.104
- It's a trap.
He read the email.

33:39.147 --> 33:40.757
He's not surrendering.

33:40.801 --> 33:42.237
- He's forcing our hand.

33:42.281 --> 33:43.804
Not knowing the meeting place
means there's no time

33:43.847 --> 33:45.893
to set backup.

33:45.936 --> 33:48.026
- We need a body double
for Ray.

33:48.069 --> 33:51.029
- No, I'm going.
I can do this.

33:51.072 --> 33:52.334
I was a cop.

33:52.378 --> 33:54.249
Who knows what he'll doif I'm not there.

33:54.293 --> 33:57.470
Please, Gabe's like my son.

33:57.513 --> 34:02.779
♪

34:02.823 --> 34:05.130
- You ride with me in your car.

34:05.173 --> 34:07.088
Send up a bird.
Make sure they follow us.

34:07.132 --> 34:08.742
♪

34:14.400 --> 34:17.185
- Whatever happens, you stay
in the car until I say so.

34:17.229 --> 34:18.404
- Sure.

34:19.318 --> 34:22.582
To be honest, I'm okaywith however this goes down.

34:22.625 --> 34:25.106
I'm not afraid to die.

34:25.150 --> 34:28.414
- No, I don't believe that.
- No, really.

34:28.457 --> 34:30.329
My girls are grown.

34:30.372 --> 34:34.202
Without Susan, I can't seemto find my footing.

34:34.246 --> 34:36.639
- [sighs heavily]

34:36.683 --> 34:39.816
For a year
after Angelyne died,

34:39.860 --> 34:42.036
I put out two coffee mugs
every morning.

34:42.080 --> 34:44.908
[tender music]

34:44.952 --> 34:46.301
- You lost your wife?

34:46.345 --> 34:51.089
♪

34:51.132 --> 34:53.917
- We have a daughter.
She's 11.

34:53.961 --> 34:56.398
- Oh, yeah?

34:56.442 --> 34:58.748
I was working so hard,
I missed that time

34:58.792 --> 35:00.924
when my girls
were growing up.

35:00.968 --> 35:03.753
Susan got it covered.

35:03.797 --> 35:05.494
She'd set the rules.

35:05.538 --> 35:07.235
She played bad cop;I got to play good cop.

35:07.279 --> 35:08.541
- [chuckles]

35:08.584 --> 35:12.153
I'm trying to play both sides.
It ain't easy.

35:12.197 --> 35:14.460
- You're probably doinga better job than you think.

35:14.503 --> 35:16.288
♪

35:16.331 --> 35:18.377
[phone rings]

35:19.682 --> 35:21.119
Gabe.

35:21.162 --> 35:22.990
- Take the next exit
at Buck Road.

35:23.033 --> 35:24.296
You're close.

35:24.339 --> 35:29.257
♪

35:29.301 --> 35:32.042
- We're exiting,
but follow cars, keep going.

35:32.086 --> 35:33.435
- Copy that.

35:33.479 --> 35:40.399
♪

35:45.708 --> 35:47.362
[phone rings]

35:47.406 --> 35:48.842
- I'm here.

35:48.885 --> 35:50.626
- You're coming up
on a farmhouse on the right--

35:50.670 --> 35:54.108
the one with a For Sale sign.
Turn in.

35:54.152 --> 35:55.892
- Farmhouse
on Willow Grove Road.

35:55.936 --> 35:59.244
♪

35:59.287 --> 36:01.289
Once we know where Gabe is,
we'll get out

36:01.333 --> 36:02.986
of the opposite side
of the car--

36:03.030 --> 36:05.424
keep a barrier
between us and him.

36:05.467 --> 36:08.992
♪

36:09.036 --> 36:11.995
[phone rings]

36:12.039 --> 36:13.475
- Both of you
get out of the car.

36:13.519 --> 36:16.565
Ray, step to the house
away from LaCroix.

36:16.609 --> 36:18.437
- Not until we see you first.

36:18.480 --> 36:22.092
♪

36:22.136 --> 36:24.660
Ray, Ray, Ray, no!
- I'm right here, Gabe!

36:24.704 --> 36:26.184
♪

36:26.227 --> 36:27.924
Come on out and talk to me.

36:27.968 --> 36:35.105
♪

36:36.281 --> 36:37.456
- You know,
I saw this place

36:37.499 --> 36:39.545
when I came to see you
four years ago?

36:39.588 --> 36:41.111
It was for sale then too.

36:41.155 --> 36:42.939
I thought it'd be a nice place
for me and Elise

36:42.983 --> 36:45.333
to fix up,
and we could raise a family.

36:45.377 --> 36:47.944
But things change,
like you, Ray.

36:47.988 --> 36:49.642
You taught me
to tell the truth,

36:49.685 --> 36:52.993
and then you went and lied.
You sold me out!

36:53.036 --> 36:55.343
I read the emails
that you sent to Peroni!

36:55.387 --> 36:58.781
- They weren't real, Gabe.
The FBI wrote them.

36:58.825 --> 37:00.305
I didn't betray you.

37:00.348 --> 37:02.481
- He's telling
the truth, Gabriel!

37:02.524 --> 37:04.961
We had to find a way
to talk to you!

37:05.005 --> 37:07.964
[tense music]

37:08.008 --> 37:11.316
♪

37:11.359 --> 37:13.753
- I got nothing
to say to you, LaCroix!

37:13.796 --> 37:15.233
- Then listen to me, Gabriel!

37:15.276 --> 37:18.192
Peroni, all those cops
who covered up

37:18.236 --> 37:21.064
what happened at the raid,
they're all going down.

37:21.108 --> 37:22.370
- In position.

37:22.414 --> 37:26.244
Glass on Clark on your signal.

37:26.287 --> 37:28.507
- He copied.
- It's true, Gabe.

37:28.550 --> 37:30.552
Everyone's gonna know
you were right.

37:30.596 --> 37:32.293
- Well, where does
that leave me?

37:32.337 --> 37:35.427
- You didn't bend!
You stayed true to yourself!

37:35.470 --> 37:38.691
Not many people can say that.
Takes courage!

37:38.734 --> 37:39.735
- [scoffs]

37:39.779 --> 37:46.655
♪

37:47.787 --> 37:49.615
Truth before all!

37:49.658 --> 37:51.094
[soft dramatic music]

37:51.138 --> 37:52.531
You lived it.

37:52.574 --> 37:59.494
♪

38:02.149 --> 38:04.456
- I killed for it.

38:04.499 --> 38:09.112
♪

38:09.156 --> 38:11.027
- It's time
to surrender, Gabriel.

38:11.071 --> 38:13.291
- Please, Gabe,
don't give them

38:13.334 --> 38:15.684
a reason to kill you.
Just give up.

38:15.728 --> 38:18.600
I love you just like you
were one of my own kids.

38:18.644 --> 38:20.646
- If you love me,
then why did you lie to me?

38:20.689 --> 38:21.690
- I didn't--

38:21.734 --> 38:23.083
- You taught me

38:23.126 --> 38:24.432
the foundational principle
of my life.

38:24.476 --> 38:27.566
If I told the truth,
good things would happen!

38:27.609 --> 38:31.134
Well, I told the truth
and look at me now!

38:31.178 --> 38:33.485
The truth destroyed my life!

38:33.528 --> 38:36.357
[dramatic music]

38:36.401 --> 38:38.141
[groans]

38:38.185 --> 38:40.796
You set me up for failure.

38:40.840 --> 38:46.976
♪

38:47.020 --> 38:48.978
I'm done.
- Don't touch it!

38:49.022 --> 38:51.981
♪

38:52.025 --> 38:54.680
Drop the belt!
Drop it!

38:54.723 --> 39:01.687
♪

39:05.995 --> 39:08.215
Gabe.
Gabe, Gabe, Gabe, Gabe!

39:08.258 --> 39:15.353
♪

39:17.442 --> 39:19.269
Put your hands on your head.

39:19.313 --> 39:20.706
- Yeah, you watch.

39:20.749 --> 39:22.447
♪

39:22.490 --> 39:25.493
You look what you did to me.

39:25.537 --> 39:26.538
- Damn it.

39:26.581 --> 39:33.109
♪

39:33.153 --> 39:34.763
- [screaming]

39:34.807 --> 39:37.244
- Oh, my God, Gabe!

39:37.287 --> 39:39.551
- [screaming]

39:41.683 --> 39:48.603
♪

39:49.909 --> 39:52.868
[screaming]

39:52.912 --> 39:59.745
♪

40:06.229 --> 40:08.797
- Bring up EMS now
and call a medevac!

40:08.841 --> 40:11.800
[somber music]

40:11.844 --> 40:18.764
♪

40:29.601 --> 40:32.734
- I'm gonna go with him.
He's got nobody else.

40:32.778 --> 40:35.694
♪

40:35.737 --> 40:39.524
- You okay?
- Just a few singed hairs.

40:39.567 --> 40:41.395
- I don't know who gets credit
for this,

40:41.439 --> 40:42.962
but the city of Newark
just settled

40:43.005 --> 40:45.921
with the family of the guy
who was killed in the raid.

40:45.965 --> 40:47.662
- Good for them.

40:47.706 --> 40:50.056
Too bad it took four livesto get it done.

40:50.099 --> 40:51.927
- Truth is a bitch.

40:51.971 --> 40:54.930
[siren blares]

40:54.974 --> 41:02.155
♪

41:04.853 --> 41:05.811
- Hey, Tali.

41:05.854 --> 41:07.334
♪

41:07.377 --> 41:08.901
What you got there?

41:10.293 --> 41:12.295
- Missy had kittens.

41:12.339 --> 41:15.124
I think she's gonna bea great mom.

41:15.168 --> 41:17.475
- I bet she will.

41:20.173 --> 41:22.784
You know, your mom
used to think

41:22.828 --> 41:25.700
before she made a decision,
any decision.

41:28.181 --> 41:29.922
Not like us.

41:32.664 --> 41:35.667
You didn't think before you
decided to wander off,

41:35.710 --> 41:38.626
and I didn't think before I
decided to ground you.

41:39.845 --> 41:44.327
So, I was thinking,
maybe we should try

41:44.371 --> 41:46.199
to be a little bit
more like Mom.

41:50.290 --> 41:52.814
Deal?

41:52.858 --> 41:54.163
- Deal.

41:54.207 --> 41:57.166
[warm music]

41:57.210 --> 42:02.607
♪

42:02.650 --> 42:04.173
See 'em?

42:04.217 --> 42:05.827
[kittens squeaking]

42:05.871 --> 42:08.264
- Ah.
- [meows]

42:08.308 --> 42:09.701
♪

42:09.744 --> 42:12.181
- I love you, Dad.

42:12.225 --> 42:14.009
- I love you too, sweetheart.

